Rhodes park accused appear in court. (Iavan Pijoos, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg -&nbsp;The trial of three men accused of raping two women and killing their husbands in Rhodes Park, Johannesburg, is expected to continue in the High Court sitting in Palm Ridge on Tuesday.Admore Ndlovu, 23, Thabo Nkala, 25, and Mduduzi Lawrence Mathibela, 32, were charged with robbery with aggravating circumstances, rape and murder. They pleaded not guilty.They were allegedly part of a 12-man gang that attacked two couples who had gone to the park, in Kensington, on the evening of Saturday, October 17, 2015, after a church service.The four were reportedly forced to lie on the ground. A knife was used to cut off the underwear of both women before they were raped.Their husbands, Zukisa Kela and Sizwe Tyeke, were forced to strip and ordered into the lake, where they drowned.The gang allegedly stole their clothes, jewellery, and cellphones. Police divers found the bodies.During a trial within a trial at their last court appearance, Mathibela told the court that officers were paid to fabricate evidence against him, including faking his DNA.Mathibela also claimed that one of the arresting officers had told him that he was going to get a bonus for the arrest.Mathibela's DNA was discovered on one of the women who were raped.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.